> Use fdisk/gdisk for discoverable partitions: https://systemd.io/DISCOVERABLE_PARTITIONS/ https://0pointer.net/blog/the-wondrous-world-of-discoverable-gpt-disk-images.html
> Use systemd-fstab-generator and scripts to automatically add mount options to fstab: https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd-fstab-generator.html#
> Use systemd-homed to make a luks home directory: https://systemd.io/HOME_DIRECTORY/ https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/homectl.html#
> A good BTRFS Arch Linux installation: https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/qw02z5/the_ideal_btrfs_setup_on_arch_linux/
> More secure booting with systemd-boot & UEFI stubs: https://linderud.dev/blog/mkinitcpio-v31-and-uefi-stubs/
> Mount ESP to /efi and additionally mount an "Extended Boot Loader Partition" (XBOOTLDR) to /boot: https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/EFI_system_partition#Typical_mount_points
> How distros should handle encryption: https://0pointer.net/blog/authenticated-boot-and-disk-encryption-on-linux.html
